Here, a relative simple method based on a measurement of transient EL of phosphor dopant was employed to determine χS in the SPF based PLED. The observation of transient EL of phosphor dopant was originally proposed to give a direct evidence of SE and TE generated in the host harvested by the phosphor50. Accordingly, transient response of phosphor emission can be described by the following equation (detailed derivations are shown in the Supplementary Information (SI)):1[T]G=A⋅exp(−tτTG)+B⋅[exp(−tτTG)−exp(−tτTHd)]\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
